"title": "4970: seasons, of the year",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4970: seasons, of the year",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Distinctive periods of the year marked by certain climatic conditions. Seasons are examples of God's perfect order in the world. They represent the balanced cycle of creation which is sustained by God and through which his provision and mercy are made known.</p>\n<h2>Seasons are appointed by God</h2>\n<h3>Seasons are created by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:16-Ps74:17\">PSA 74:16–74:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:14\">GEN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:19\">PSA 104:19</a></p>\n<h3>Seasons are sustained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:24\">JER 5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:32-Job38:33\">JOB 38:32–38:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:26\">EZK 34:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:17\">ACT 14:17</a></p>\n<h2>The agricultural seasons of Palestine</h2>\n<h3>The dry and rainy seasons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:23\">JOL 2:23</a></strong> <em>The rainy season, accounting for over 90 per cent of the national rainfall, runs from October to March/April. Its beginning is marked by the autumn rains in October/November; the lighter spring showers in April/May announce the coming of the dry season.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:13\">EZR 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:3\">HOS 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:7\">JAS 5:7</a>LEV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas26:3-Jas26:4\">26:3–26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:13-Deut11:14\">DEU 11:13–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:12\">DEU 28:12</a></p>\n<h3>Seedtime and harvest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:4\">PRO 20:4</a></strong> <em>Ploughing and sowing take place from October to December when the autumn rains have begun to soften the ground. Most crops are harvested between April and June.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:21\">EXO 34:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:20\">NUM 13:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:26\">JOB 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:3\">PSA 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Spring</h2>\n<h3>Spring rain as a sign of blessing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:23\">JOB 29:23</a> <em>The gentle spring rains signal the approach of harvest</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:15\">PRO 16:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:3\">JER 3:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:1\">ZEC 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>Spring as a time of growth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:11-Song2:13\">SNG 2:11–2:13</a></strong> <em>Spring marks a pleasant interval between the heavy winter rains and the onset of the dry season.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:25\">PRO 27:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:22\">JOL 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32\">MAT 24:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28\">MRK 13:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:29-Luke21:30\">LUK 21:29–21:30</a></p>\n<h3>Spring as a time for war</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:1\">2SA 11:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:1\">1CH 20:1</a> <em>The time following the spring harvest (May/June), when agricultural commitments are reduced</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:26\">1KI 20:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:20\">2KI 13:20</a></p>\n<h3>Festivals celebrated in spring</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5-Lev23:6\">LEV 23:5–23:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:16-Num28:17\">NUM 28:16–28:17</a> <em>Passover and Unleavened Bread</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:10\">LEV 23:10</a> <em>offering the firstfruits of the barley harvest</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:15-Lev23:16\">LEV 23:15–23:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:9-Deut16:10\">DEU 16:9–16:10</a> <em>The Feast of Weeks celebrated the ingathering of the grain harvest.</em></p>\n<h2>Summer</h2>\n<h3>A period of intense heat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:4\">PSA 32:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:17\">JOB 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>A time for harvesting summer fruit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:20\">JER 8:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:5\">PRO 10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:10-Jer40:12\">JER 40:10–40:12</a> <em>Grapes, olives and figs are harvested in July/September</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:1\">MIC 7:1</a></p>\n<h3>A time to store harvested grain</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:8\">PRO 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:25\">PRO 30:25</a></p>\n<h2>Autumn</h2>\n<h3>The breaking of the summer drought</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:6\">PSA 84:6</a></strong> <em>Autumn is the start of the rainy season and corresponds to the time of ploughing and sowing.</em></p>\n<h3>Festivals celebrated in autumn</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:24\">LEV 23:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:1\">NUM 29:1</a> <em>the Feast of Trumpets</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:27\">LEV 23:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7\">NUM 29:7</a> <em>the Day of Atonement</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34\">LEV 23:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a> <em>the Feast of Tabernacles</em></p>\n<h2>Winter</h2>\n<h3>A time of inclement weather</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:6-Job37:10\">JOB 37:6–37:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:10\">ISA 55:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:22\">JER 36:22</a></p>\n<h3>A time when travelling is difficult</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:20\">MAT 24:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:18\">MRK 13:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:21\">2TI 4:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:12\">ACT 27:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:6\">1CO 16:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:12\">TIT 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Celebration of the Feast of Dedication</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:22\">JHN 10:22</a> <em>The Feast of Dedication (Hannukah) commemorates the rededication of the temple by Judas Maccabeus in 165 B.C.</em></p>",
